      "date": "2012-11-22 05:01:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, approved\n\nMinor style note: for console errors, the preferred format is to print the device name at the beginning, and the error code at the end like:\n\n CERRROR(\"%s: ... message: rc = %d\\n\", device_name, rc);\n\nIn this case of global parameters there is not a device name that can be printed, so that part can be skipped, but we're trying to make the message content more useful and consistent we go along.\n\nNot a fatal reason to reject the patch, but would be nice to fix if the patch is resubmitted.\n\nA similar patch is needed for b2_1 as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
